{"body": "@josevalim I would like to mention that the approach I have taken with this patch (to push more work about maintaining associations onto the developer and to not try and keep the IM in sync with changes to the DB made by straight SQL) means that the IM is much less invasive. I will clean up this patch and you will see that only 4 or 5 core ActiveRecord classes are affected in very small ways.\n\nThe performance and consistency benefits of the IM are huge IMHO. I will post to the Rails mailing list soon.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7264495", "created_at": "2012-07-25T22:39:17Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6524#issuecomment-7264495", "updated_at": "2012-07-25T22:39:17Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6524, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/sskirby", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/4d4c378e3a10e2d01a636a33c359734c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6f3e24662182e125fc58299809ee6a67.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4d4c378e3a10e2d01a636a33c359734c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "sskirby", "type": "User", "id": 25760, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sskirby/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523e4e93bd354364b900ee8d"}, "id": 7264495, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6524"}
